{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"grumpy-site-beard","description":"## Summary\nA work ticket carries a single cryptographic attestation slot (`state[\"signature\"]`). Both the **plan-review attestation** (earned at claim time via `rebar review-plan`) and the **completion verdict** (signed at close by the completion verifier) are written as `SIGNATURE` events into that one slot. The reducer applies `SIGNATURE` as last-writer-wins, so the completion verdict signed on close **overwrites and destroys** the plan-review attestation. These two attestations are independent proofs of two different gates and should be **additive** — a closed ticket should retain BOTH.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Take a non-bug work ticket (e.g. a `story`) and earn a plan-review attestation: `rebar review-plan <id>` (PASS). `rebar show <id>` now shows `signature.manifest[0] == \"plan-review: PASS\"`.\n2. Claim and complete the work, then close: `rebar transition <id> in_progress closed`. The completion verifier runs and signs a completion verdict.\n3. `rebar show <id>` again.\n\n**Expected:** the ticket retains both attestations — the plan-review PASS *and* the completion-verifier PASS (queryable independently).\n\n**Actual:** the `signature` field now shows only `manifest[0] == \"completion-verifier: PASS\"`; the plan-review attestation is gone from compiled state. Observed live on story `3d3d-da49-c3f3-4298` (REB-522): `signature` was `[\"plan-review: PASS\", ...]` while in_progress and became `[\"completion-verifier: PASS\", ...]` after close.\n\n## Root Cause\n`src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:376` `process_signature()` does `state[\"signature\"] = {…}` — a single slot, last-writer-wins (see its own docstring, line 377). The compactor builds the SNAPSHOT `compiled_state` via this same reducer, so after compaction the earlier attestation is permanently lost from compiled state (the raw append-only SIGNATURE events still exist in the log, but `show`/MCP/`verify-signature`/the gates read the single compiled field). Both verdict kinds are already distinguishable by `manifest[0]` (`\"plan-review: …\"` vs `\"completion-verifier: …\"`), so they can be keyed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A ticket can simultaneously hold a plan-review attestation AND a completion verdict; signing one does not clobber the other (additive, not last-writer-wins across kinds).\n- [ ] Within a single kind, last-writer-wins still applies (re-running plan-review replaces the prior plan-review attestation; re-closing replaces the prior completion verdict).\n- [ ] `process_signature` (and the SNAPSHOT/compaction path that replays it) preserves all kinds across compaction.\n- [ ] `verify-signature` can certify each attestation kind; the claim gate reads the plan-review attestation and the close gate reads/writes the completion verdict, each unaffected by the presence of the other.\n- [ ] Backward compatible: tickets with a single legacy `signature` still verify; the change is forward/back-compat for older clones (new shape preserved-and-ignored, per the rollout convention).\n- [ ] Tests cover: plan-review then close retains both; re-sign same kind replaces in place; round-trip through compaction; legacy single-signature ticket still reads/verifies.\n\n## Affected Files (initial)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (`process_signature`)\n- `src/rebar/signing.py` (`sign_manifest`, verify)\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py`, `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` (signing call sites)\n- relevant SIGNATURE schema under `src/rebar/schemas/` and reducer/compaction tests","id":"e6a0-ba9b-ae92-43d7","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"Completion verdict signature clobbers the plan-review attestation (single signature slot is last-writer-wins; should be additive)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782752300160229001,"uuid":"3d18f61b-7fe0-4b1f-a1ad-75ecb62ec4a6"}